    div.dapgray.ph4.pv2
      div.container(style="max-width: none; padding: 0px;")
        div.row
          div.col-sm
            a(href='/').imgstyle.daplogo
              img(src='https://raw.githubusercontent.com/aepyornis/dap-dr/master/dashboard/dapdrlogo.png').daplogo
    div.intro
      p 
        span Community groups, organizers, residents, and policymakers play a critical role in preventing tenant harassment and displacement 
        | in rent stabilized buildings. However, existing data and information is fragmented and often confusing, and identifying which 
        | New York City buildings are most vulnerable can be a challenge. 
      p
        span DAP District Reports are a part of the 
        a.light(href='http://anhd.org' target='_blank') Association for Neighborhood & Housing Development’s 
        span (ANHD) 
        a.light(href='http://dapmapnyc.org' target='_blank')  Displacement Alert Project 
        span  (DAP), leveraging data and visualizations to help protect tenants and preserve New York City’s stock of affordable housing.
      p 
        span Our DAP District Reports provide up-to-date information on where rent stabilized tenants are at greatest risk of displacement 
        | in each community district. Buildings that appear on multiple lists are coded 
        span.dapyellow.black.ph1 yellow
        span , 
        span.daporange.black.ph1 orange
        span , or 
        span.dapred.white.ph1.lighttext red
        span , depending on the level of risk. We determine risk based on public data on 
        span.medtext new property sales
        span , 
        span.medtext HPD complaints
        span , 
        span.medtext HPD violations
        span , 
        span.medtext DOB complaints
        span , and 
        span.medtext DOB construction permit applications. 
      p
        span With DAP District Reports, you can:
          ul.lh-copy
            li Access community district-level data on at-risk buildings
            li View reports on your computer, phone, or print them out in a clear format to take offline and into the field
            li Look back at reports from previous months
            li Navigate directly to a property page on ACRIS, HPD, DOB, DOF tax bills, OASIS map, and Google Maps
    for boro in districts
      div.fl.w-100.ph4
        div.f4.pv2.black #{boro[0]} 
        for district in boro[1]
          div.fl.mb2.f6.links.w-90
            a(href=`${district.cd}.html`) 
              span #{district.name}: &nbsp;
              | #{district.neighborhoods}
